Brazil Daybook: Abril Educacao Sells Shares Below Estimated Price Range

-- B y   R o b i n   S t r i n g e r
-- 
2011-07-22T07:58:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-22/brazil-daybook-abril-educacao-sells-shares-below-estimated-price-range.html
Abril Educacao SA, a Brazilian
education and publishing group, sold shares at 20 reais in an
initial public offering, below the estimated price range of
21.75 reais to 26.75 reais set in its prospectus.  At least eight companies have shelved first-time sales in
 Brazil  this year before yesterday, data compiled by Bloomberg
and the securities regulator show.  GOVERNMENT:
*President Dilma Rousseff has internal meetings starting at 9
a.m.
*Finance Minister Guido Mantega meets with the board of
Petrobras in Brasilia at 10:30 a.m.
*Central bank president Alexandre Tombini has meetings in
Brasilia.  WHAT TO WATCH:
*Creditors of Independencia, the meatpacker operating under
 bankruptcy protection  with an estimated 1.9 billion reais of
debt, vote on bids for its assets.  EQUITIES:
*OSX (OSXB3 BZ) entered into a pact worth $800 million with
Modec Inc. for the construction of its FPSO unit, OSX-3. *Gafisa
(GFSA3 BZ) led a rally for Brazilian homebuilders yesterday
after the central bank signaled it may stop raising  interest
rates , boosting the outlook for demand.  MARKETS
*The Bovespa index rose 1.9 percent to 60,262.95
*The real rose 0.8 percent to 1.5526 per dollar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
